p <- ggplot(mtcars, aes(mpg, wt, colour = cyl)) + geom_point()
p <-  p + labs(colour = "Cylinders")

plotly::ggplotly(p)

# Add tag

The plot tag appears at the top-left, and is typically used for labelling a subplot with a letter.

<pre class="mcode">
p <- ggplot(mtcars, aes(mpg, wt, colour = cyl)) + geom_point()
p <-  p + labs(title = "title", tag = "A")

plotly::ggplotly(p)

# How to remove label


<pre class="mcode">
p <- ggplot(mtcars, aes(mpg, wt, colour = cyl)) + geom_point()
p <-    
 p +
 labs(title = "title") +
 labs(title = NULL)
 
plotly::ggplotly(p)
